<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="282" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="4.[136,1452,1728,2079]" pageId="4" pageNumber="282">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[136,261,1728,1754]" pageId="4" pageNumber="282">Diagnosis:</emphasis>
—Basidiocarps large and stout, pileus pilose-squamulose, pale brownish grey or ochre brown, volva spacious, saccate, ochre brown or with olive tint, with velvety outer surface; basidiospores 7.5–8.5(9.3) × 5.0–6.0(6.4) µm, broadly ellipsoid to ovoid, cheilocystidia lageniform or fusiform, with apical papilla (mucronate), caulocystidia numerous; grow on rotten wood or litter.
</paragraph>
