<paragraph blockId="5.[136,1452,1756,2071]" lastBlockId="6.[136,1452,158,1229]" lastPageId="6" lastPageNumber="284" pageId="5" pageNumber="283">
<emphasis box="[189,347,1757,1783]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="283">Basidiospores</emphasis>
[60, 1, 1] 7.5–8.5(9.3) × 5.0–6.0(6.4) µm (L 
<subScript attach="left" box="[871,886,1776,1790]" fontSize="6" pageId="5" pageNumber="283">av</subScript>
= 8.3 µm, W 
<subScript attach="left" box="[1046,1061,1776,1790]" fontSize="6" pageId="5" pageNumber="283">av</subScript>
= 5.7 µm, Q = (1.3)1.4–1.6(1.7), Q 
<subScript attach="left" box="[156,171,1812,1826]" fontSize="6" pageId="5" pageNumber="283">av</subScript>
= 1.5), ellipsoid to broadly ellipsoid or ovoid, hyaline in KOH, thick-walled. 
<emphasis box="[1065,1151,1793,1819]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="283">Basidia</emphasis>
24–30(40) × 7–10 µm, 4- spored, broadly clavate, often inflated in the middle. 
<emphasis box="[750,912,1829,1855]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="283">Cheilocystidia</emphasis>
(40)57–93(110) × 13.5–20(40) µm, numerous, forming a sterile lamella edge, ventricose-fusiform, broadly lageniform, often with apical papilla (mucronate), thin- or slightly thick-walled, hyaline in 3% KOH, often with granular content. 
<emphasis box="[958,1120,1901,1927]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="283">Pleurocystidia</emphasis>
40–80(98) × 13–20(28) µm, rather abundant, ventricose-fusiform or lageniform with obtuse or subcapitate apex, slightly thick-walled, hyaline in 3% KOH. 
<emphasis box="[260,429,1973,1999]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="283">Lamella trama</emphasis>
composed of hyaline hyphae 3–7 µm wide, thin-walled. 
<emphasis box="[1092,1206,1973,1999]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="283">Pileipellis</emphasis>
a cutis, transforming into a trichoderm, made up of thin- or slightly thick-walled, non-gelatinous hyphae, 15–20(30) µm wide, hyaline or yellowish; ascending terminal elements are cylindrical or fusiform with acuminate or mucronate apex, 70–200(290) µm long. 
<emphasis box="[253,381,158,184]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="284">Stipitipellis</emphasis>
a cutis, compose of long, cylindrical, hyaline hyphae, 8–10 µm wide. 
<emphasis box="[1219,1375,158,184]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="284">Caulocystidia</emphasis>
rather numerous, 30–84(92) × (5.5)7.0–18 µm, in bundles, cylindrical, fusiform or lageniform, hyaline, thin-walled. 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="284">Clamp connections</emphasis>
absent in all tissues examined.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[136,1452,158,1229]" pageId="6" pageNumber="284">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,594,266,292]" pageId="6" pageNumber="284">Habitat and known distribution:</emphasis>
—Solitary, on banana litter in woody area. So far known only from two provinces of 
<collectingCountry box="[282,377,302,328]" name="Vietnam" pageId="6" pageNumber="284">Vietnam</collectingCountry>
located in central and southern parts of the country.
</paragraph>
