<paragraph blockId="6.[136,1452,158,1229]" pageId="6" pageNumber="284">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,265,518,544]" pageId="6" pageNumber="284">Notes:</emphasis>
— 
<materialsCitation collectorName="Thorough &amp; However &amp; Another &amp; E. Popov &amp; This &amp; Here" country="Vietnam" location="Nghe An province" pageId="6" pageNumber="284" specimenCount="1" stateProvince="Nghe An">
During the expedition to 
<collectingCountry box="[567,662,518,544]" name="Vietnam" pageId="6" pageNumber="284">Vietnam</collectingCountry>
in 2016, 
<specimenCount box="[762,913,518,545]" pageId="6" pageNumber="284" type="generic">one specimen</specimenCount>
of a presumably unknown species was collected. 
<collectorName box="[136,246,554,580]" pageId="6" pageNumber="284">Thorough</collectorName>
morphological and molecular study has shown its uniqueness and independent taxonomic status (
<bibRefCitation author="Malysheva, E. &amp; Malysheva, V. &amp; Alexandrova, A. &amp; Morozova, O." pageId="6" pageNumber="284" pagination="233 - 254" refId="ref6958" refString="Malysheva, E., Malysheva, V., Alexandrova, A. &amp; Morozova, O. (2019) Observations on Pluteaceae in Vietnam. 1. New species and new records of Volvariella. Phytotaxa 408 (4): 233 - 254. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / phytotaxa. 408.4.1" type="journal article" year="2019">
Malysheva 
<emphasis box="[136,191,590,616]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="284">et al.</emphasis>
2019
</bibRefCitation>
). 
<collectorName box="[275,379,591,617]" pageId="6" pageNumber="284">However</collectorName>
, this specimen was immature, and then we could not study in detail the features of basidiospores. 
<collectorName box="[136,228,626,652]" pageId="6" pageNumber="284">Another</collectorName>
collection, found by one of the co-authors (
<collectorName box="[731,837,626,653]" pageId="6" pageNumber="284">E. Popov</collectorName>
) in 
<collectingRegion box="[883,1091,626,652]" country="Vietnam" name="Nghe An" pageId="6" pageNumber="284">Nghe An province</collectingRegion>
of 
<collectingCountry box="[1131,1226,626,652]" name="Vietnam" pageId="6" pageNumber="284">Vietnam</collectingCountry>
in 2019, turned out to be identical to the previous one. 
<collectorName box="[528,578,662,688]" pageId="6" pageNumber="284">This</collectorName>
made it possible to clarify the lacking morphological characteristics. 
<collectorName box="[1357,1411,663,689]" pageId="6" pageNumber="284">Here</collectorName>
we describe a new species, providing an amended and combined description based on the two studied collections
</materialsCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[136,1452,158,1229]" pageId="6" pageNumber="284">
The macroscopic characteristics of our collections mostly agree with the description of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Singer" authorityYear="1949" baseAuthorityName="Schaeffer" baseAuthorityYear="1774" box="[1170,1423,734,760]" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Pluteaceae" genus="Volvariella" kingdom="Fungi" order="Agaricales" pageId="6" pageNumber="284" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="bombycina">
<emphasis box="[1170,1423,734,760]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="284">Volvariella bombycina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in terms of stout basidiocarps with light-coloured pale brownish and entirely squamulose pileus, thick stipe, and spacious brown volva. At the same time, the microscopic characters, such as the size of basidiospores and the peculiar form of cheilocystidia with the apical papilla, make it close to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Singer" authorityYear="1949" baseAuthorityName="Bulliard" baseAuthorityYear="1786" box="[761,890,842,868]" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Pluteaceae" genus="Volvariella" kingdom="Fungi" order="Agaricales" pageId="6" pageNumber="284" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="volvacea">
<emphasis box="[761,890,842,868]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="284">V. volvacea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="E. F. Malysheva, E. S. Popov &amp; A. V. Alexandrova" authorityYear="2022" box="[906,1145,842,868]" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Pluteaceae" genus="Volvariella" kingdom="Fungi" order="Agaricales" pageId="6" pageNumber="284" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="orientalis">
<emphasis box="[906,1145,842,868]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="284">Volvariella orientalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Singer" authorityYear="1949" baseAuthorityName="Schaeffer" baseAuthorityYear="1774" box="[1299,1451,842,868]" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Pluteaceae" genus="Volvariella" kingdom="Fungi" order="Agaricales" pageId="6" pageNumber="284" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="bombycina">
<emphasis box="[1299,1451,842,868]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="284">V. bombycina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in velvety outer surface of volva and broader hymenial cystidia with subcapitate apex, and it mainly differs from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Singer" authorityYear="1949" baseAuthorityName="Bulliard" baseAuthorityYear="1786" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Pluteaceae" genus="Volvariella" kingdom="Fungi" order="Agaricales" pageId="6" pageNumber="284" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="volvacea">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="284">V. volvacea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in pilose-squamulose pileus, ochre brown or olive brown volva and the presence of caulocystidia (
<bibRefCitation author="Boekhout, T." pageId="6" pageNumber="284" pagination="56 - 64" refId="ref4422" refString="Boekhout, T. (1990) Volvariella. In: Bas, C., Kuyper, Th. W., Noordeloos, M. E. &amp; Vellinga, E. C. (Eds.) Flora Agaricina Neerlandica 2. A. A. Balkema, Rotterdam, pp. 56 - 64." type="book chapter" year="1990">Boekhout 1990</bibRefCitation>
). Moreover, the phylogenetic analyses of the combined nrITS and nrLSU sequences demonstrate the independent position of these three species on the tree (
<figureCitation box="[613,678,986,1012]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[136,229,1842,1864]" captionTargetBox="[152,1388,203,1811]" captionTargetId="figure-24@3.[151,1436,190,1818]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1.—Best tree from the ML analysis of the nrITS-nrLSU dataset for Volvariella species, with Cantharocybe gruberi as outgroup. Bootstrap support values and Posterior probability (BS/PP) are given above the branches.All tips are labelled with taxon name and voucher or strain numbers. For taxon in bold the sequences are generated in present study." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6541460" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6541460/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="284">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[136,1452,158,1229]" pageId="6" pageNumber="284">
The macromorphology of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="E. F. Malysheva, E. S. Popov &amp; A. V. Alexandrova" authorityYear="2022" box="[479,612,1022,1048]" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Pluteaceae" genus="Volvariella" kingdom="Fungi" order="Agaricales" pageId="6" pageNumber="284" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="orientalis">
<emphasis box="[479,612,1022,1048]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="284">V. orientalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
makes it also close to 
<taxonomicName authority="(Berk. &amp; Broome 1871: 151) Singer (1949: 401)" authorityName="Singer" authorityPageNumber="401" authorityYear="1949" baseAuthorityName="Berk. &amp; Broome" baseAuthorityPageNumber="151" baseAuthorityYear="1871" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Pluteaceae" genus="Volvariella" kingdom="Fungi" order="Agaricales" pageId="6" pageNumber="284" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="diplasia">
<emphasis box="[855,970,1022,1048]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="284">V. diplasia</emphasis>
(Berk. &amp; Broome 1871: 151) 
<bibRefCitation author="Singer, R." pageId="6" pageNumber="284" pagination="1 - 832" refId="ref7787" refString="Singer, R. (1949) The Agaricales in modern taxonomy. Lilloa 22: 1 - 832." type="journal article" year="1949">Singer (1949: 401)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, edible mushroom species currently cultivated in both tropical and subtropical regions. The main differences between the two species are colour of the volva, shape and size of basidiospores and cheilocystidia. The volva of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Singer" authorityYear="1949" baseAuthorityName="Berk. &amp; Broome" baseAuthorityYear="1871" box="[136,255,1130,1156]" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Pluteaceae" genus="Volvariella" kingdom="Fungi" order="Agaricales" pageId="6" pageNumber="284" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="diplasia">
<emphasis box="[136,255,1130,1156]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="284">V. diplasia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is more light coloured, while 
<taxonomicName authorityName="E. F. Malysheva, E. S. Popov &amp; A. V. Alexandrova" authorityYear="2022" box="[604,740,1130,1156]" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Pluteaceae" genus="Volvariella" kingdom="Fungi" order="Agaricales" pageId="6" pageNumber="284" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="orientalis">
<emphasis box="[604,740,1130,1156]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="284">V. orientalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has dark brown volva with distinct olive tint; the spores of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Singer" authorityYear="1949" baseAuthorityName="Berk. &amp; Broome" baseAuthorityYear="1871" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Pluteaceae" genus="Volvariella" kingdom="Fungi" order="Agaricales" pageId="6" pageNumber="284" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="diplasia">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="284">V. diplasia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are more elongate, often subcylindrical and frequently 10 µm or longer, and cheilocystidia are piriform or clavate and significantly smaller (33–50 × 18–26 µm) (Pegler 1987) than ones in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="E. F. Malysheva, E. S. Popov &amp; A. V. Alexandrova" authorityYear="2022" box="[1049,1183,1202,1228]" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Pluteaceae" genus="Volvariella" kingdom="Fungi" order="Agaricales" pageId="6" pageNumber="284" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="orientalis">
<emphasis box="[1049,1183,1202,1228]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="284">V. orientalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
